------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    ### GROUP BY ###

mysql> select author_id,count(author_id) 
from books group by author_id;

+-----------+------------------+
| author_id | count(author_id) |
+-----------+------------------+
|        11 |                3 |
|        15 |                2 |
|        14 |                1 |
|        12 |                1 |
|        13 |                1 |
+-----------+------------------+

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    ### UNION ### (Duplicate records does not display)

Q .write a query to get title , type of books table and 
   first_name,last_name of authors table and display by combining both the 
   table records in title , type columns.

mysql> select title, type from books 
        UNION select first_name,last_name 
        from authors;

+------------------+------------+
| title            | type       |
+------------------+------------+
| Time to Grow Up! | original   |
| Your Trip        | translated |
| Lovely Love      | original   |
| Dream Your Life  | original   |
| Oranges          | translated |
| Your Happy Life  | translated |
| Applied AI       | translated |
| My Last Book     | original   |
| Ellen            | Writer     |
| Olga             | Savelieva  |
| Jack             | Smart      |
| Donald           | Brain      |
| Yao              | Dou        |
+------------------+------------+

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    ### UNION ALL ### (we also got duplicate records)

Q .write a query to get title , type of books table and 
   first_name,last_name of authors table and display by combining both the 
   table records in title , type columns.

mysql> select title, type from books UNION ALL
     select first_name,last_name from authors;

+------------------+------------+
| title            | type       |
+------------------+------------+
| Time to Grow Up! | original   |
| Your Trip        | translated |
| Lovely Love      | original   |
| Dream Your Life  | original   |
| Oranges          | translated |
| Your Happy Life  | translated |
| Applied AI       | translated |
| My Last Book     | original   |
| Ellen            | Writer     |
| Olga             | Savelieva  |
| Jack             | Smart      |
| Donald           | Brain      |
| Yao              | Dou        |
| Ellen            | Writer     |
+------------------+------------+


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    ### ORDER BY ###
mysql> select title, type from books UNION
        select first_name,last_name 
        from authors ORDER BY title;

+------------------+------------+
| title            | type       |
+------------------+------------+
| Applied AI       | translated |
| Donald           | Brain      |
| Dream Your Life  | original   |
| Ellen            | Writer     |
| Jack             | Smart      |
| Lovely Love      | original   |
| My Last Book     | original   |
| Olga             | Savelieva  |
| Oranges          | translated |
| Time to Grow Up! | original   |
| Yao              | Dou        |
| Your Happy Life  | translated |
| Your Trip        | translated |
+------------------+------------+


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    ### GROUP BY ###
Q. Write a query to get count of records in type column of books table.

mysql> select type, COUNT(type) 
        from books GROUP BY type;

+------------+-------------+
| type       | COUNT(type) |
+------------+-------------+
| original   |           4 |
| translated |           4 |
+------------+-------------+


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    ### HAVING ###

Q. Write a query to get count of records in author_id column having author_id is 
   greater than 13of books table.

mysql> select author_id, COUNT(author_id) 
        from books GROUP BY author_id 
        HAVING author_id>13;

+-----------+------------------+
| author_id | COUNT(author_id) |
+-----------+------------------+
|        15 |                2 |
|        14 |                1 |
+-----------+------------------+


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q. Write a query to get all record from books table who having minimun author_id.

mysql> select * from books where 
        author_id=(select MIN(author_id) 
        from books);

+----+------------------+----------+-----------+-----------+---------------+
| id | title            | type     | author_id | editor_id | translator_id |
+----+------------------+----------+-----------+-----------+---------------+
|  1 | Time to Grow Up! | original |        11 |        21 |          NULL |
|  4 | Dream Your Life  | original |        11 |        24 |          NULL |
|  8 | My Last Book     | original |        11 |        28 |          NULL |
+----+------------------+----------+-----------+-----------+---------------+


